================================================================================
NOTE ON DATA AND THIRD-PARTY ASSETS
================================================================================

The MIT terms above cover the source code only. The quote datasets and some
third-party assets carry separate terms.

1. Quote datasets (data/, firmware/data/)

   a. Public-domain excerpts (kind=원문)
      Drawn from Korean modern literature whose copyright has expired, via
      ko.wikisource.org. Public domain.

   b. Translated excerpts (kind=역)
      Derived from the literature-clock dataset
      https://github.com/JohannesNE/literature-clock
      licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 2.5
      https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/
      The entries here are translated into Korean and re-keyed by minute, so
      they are a modified derivative. Under ShareAlike they are redistributed
      under the same CC BY-NC-SA 2.5 license, and for non-commercial use only.

      The novel excerpts underlying those entries remain the copyright of their
      respective authors and publishers. The CC license applies to the dataset
      compilation and does not replace those rights.

2. Fonts and sprite artwork

   Not distributed in this repository. The font TTF files, the generated LVGL
   font C arrays, and the icon pool bank are gitignored and fetched or built
   locally. Anyone building this project supplies those assets themselves and
   is bound by their own licenses.

3. Vendor-derived driver code

   Parts of firmware/main (display_st7305.cpp, adc_battery.cpp, shtc3.cpp) are
   ported from the Waveshare ESP32-S3-RLCD-4.2 example code
   https://github.com/waveshareteam/ESP32-S3-RLCD-4.2
   and follow that project terms.

4. Concept

   The literature-clock idea originates with Jaap Meijers and the Author Clock
   project.
